## Create an application

```
Definition
```

```http
POST /v3/apps HTTP/1.1
```

```
Example Request
```

```shell
curl "https://api.[your-domain.com]/v3/apps" \
  -X POST \
  -H "Authorization: bearer [token]"
  -d '{
        "name": "my_app",
        "environment_variables": {
          "open":"source"
        },
        "lifecycle": {
          "type": "buildpack",
          "data": {
            "stack": null,
            "buildpack": "name-2446"
          }
        },
        "relationships": {
          "space": {
            "guid":"7d3c05f1-aa8d-44cd-af6f-06e2ab1fccc1"
          }
        }
      }'
```

```
Example Response
```

```http
HTTP/1.1 201 Created

<%= yield_content :create_app, '/v3/apps' %>
```
Creates an app in v3 of the Cloud Controller API. Apps must have a valid space guid for creation, which is namespaced under {"relationships": {"space": "your-space-guid"} }. See the example for more information.

